Istanbul May Get $1 Billion for Ferry Firm IDO, Milliyet Says

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-04-08T06:24:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/istanbul-may-get-1-billion-for-ferry-firm-ido-milliyet-says.html
Istanbul municipality may raise as
much as $1 billion in today’s auction to sell its ferry company
Istanbul Deniz Otobusleri AS, known as IDO, Milliyet reported,
citing unidentified analysts.   Five investors who bid for IDO by the March 31 deadline
were a consortium between Akfen Holding AS, Souter Investments
LLP, Tepe Insaat Sanayi AS and Sera Gayrimenkul Yatirim &
Isletme AS, Global Liman Isletmeleri AS, a joint venture between
units of Koc Holding AS and  Sweden ’s Stena AB, Torunlar Gida
Sanayi & Ticaret AS and Yildirim Holding AS.   IDO which runs high-speed ferries within Istanbul and
nearby towns, provides 40 percent of Istanbul’s public
transportation by sea, according to the Istanbul-based
newspaper.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
